metadata.evaluation_name: Unified Synthesis: KW-PE Expressiveness vs Downstream Failure Gap Analysis
metadata.description: Synthesizes 4 experiments to explain why trajectory methods achieve 100% discrimination, why EDMD-based KW-PE fails downstream, and positions nRWPE as minimal spectral-invariance-breaking PE.

conditioning.detail: Median condition number ~10^21 exceeds double precision limit (~10^16), destroying all numerical information

scale_mismatch.detail: EDMD-processed PEs may have extreme scale variation due to ill-conditioning

information_content.detail: Degree-2 polynomial dictionary creates redundant lifted features, amplifying conditioning issues

RWPE.key_weakness: Cannot distinguish cospectral graphs or CSL pairs

LapPE.key_weakness: Sign ambiguity from eigenvector decomposition, not equivariant

nRWPE_tanh.key_weakness: Lower overall discrimination than full KW-PE pipeline

KW_PE_tanh.key_weakness: Catastrophic EDMD conditioning destroys downstream usability

expressiveness_downstream_correlation.interpretation: Weak/negative correlation suggests higher expressiveness does NOT guarantee better downstream performance

key_findings.finding_1: Walk topology is necessary and sufficient for 100% discrimination (A2=0% proves topology essential; A1=A3=100% proves EDMD adds no binary discrimination power)
key_findings.finding_2: EDMD conditioning catastrophic: median condition number ~10^21 for degree-2 dictionaries, exceeding double precision limit
key_findings.finding_3: nRWPE (81.7% discrimination, equivariant, eigendecomp-free) is a more practically useful contribution than full KW-PE (100% but numerically unstable)
key_findings.finding_4: Expressiveness-downstream correlation is weak/negative (Spearman rho=0.400), challenging the assumption that higher expressiveness implies better downstream performance
key_findings.finding_5: 525-pair benchmark is saturated for trajectory methods (all A1-A6 achieve 100% with large margins)
